# Publishing plan — `docs/site` static documentation

## Goals

- Ship a **version-controlled** HTML/CSS/JS site that can be published to **any static host** with zero build.
- Document **one canonical URL** after publish (update `Plugin URI`, readme links, and optional `plugin_row_meta`).
- Keep **WordPress.org** as the primary distribution channel; the static site is **companion** documentation.

## Non-goals

- Server-side rendering, databases, or WordPress-as-doc-host (unless you choose that separately).
- Coupling publish pipeline to a single vendor; the plan lists alternatives.

## Architecture overview

```
docs/site/           → artifact root (index.html + assets/)
        ↓
   static host (HTTPS)
```

**Path dependency:** CSS/JS use relative URLs (`assets/css/main.css`). Publish with **`docs/site` as the site root** so paths resolve. If you must publish from a subpath (e.g. `example.com/docs/`), add a `<base href="...">` or switch to root-relative paths (`/assets/...`) and configure the host accordingly.

## API compatibility notes

- Documentation describes **admin-ajax** actions in the current `rest-api-route-tester.php`. When you change handlers or `wprrt_vars`, update `api.html` and bump a note in changelog.
- No runtime API between the static site and WordPress; no CORS concerns.

## File-by-file change list (publishing-related)

| Path | When to change |
|------|----------------|
| `rest-api-route-tester.php` | Set `Plugin URI` to the live docs or marketing URL once stable. |
| `README.md` | Keep “Documentation” link in sync with published URL. |
| `readme.txt` | Optional one-line pointer to docs URL for .org (HTTPS only). |
| `docs/site/*.html` | Replace relative links if switching to absolute URLs for SEO. |

## PR breakdown

1. **Merge** the static site + `SITE_PUBLISHING_PLAN.mdc` (this file) + `docs/site/README.md`.
2. **Choose host** (below) and run a **staging** deploy (branch or preview URL).
3. **Smoke test:** home, dev, api pages; mobile menu; fonts load; no mixed content.
4. **Go live:** point DNS or enable custom domain; set canonical URL in plugin header on next release.

## Test plan (pre–go-live)

- [ ] All internal links work on the deployed origin (not only `file://` or localhost).
- [ ] `assets/css/main.css` and `assets/js/main.js` return 200 (check Network tab).
- [ ] Lighthouse: no critical accessibility regressions (skip link, nav labels).
- [ ] Optional: [validator.w3.org](https://validator.w3.org/) on each HTML file.

## Migration / backfill

- **First publish:** no data migration.
- **If changing hosts:** update links once; old URLs can redirect at the DNS/CDN layer.

